modules.description: Handles HTTP requests with thread-based concurrency, offering routing based on URL paths, parsing and generating URL-encoded data, and serving static files from a directory. Supports streaming responses and server-sent events, with optional gzip compression via camlzip. Ideal for lightweight web backends or embedded systems requiring minimal dependencies.

Provides deflate compression and decompression for HTTP responses using camlzip. Works with stream and fixed-size body data, compressing only when the content length exceeds a specified threshold. Installs middleware to enable compression in a Tiny_httpd server, using a configurable buffer size for efficiency.
